==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pisolite
<hw>Pi"so*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a pea +
<ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pisolithe</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A variety of calcite, or calcium carbonate, consisting of
aggregated globular concretions about the size of a pea; -- called also
<altname>peastone</altname>, <altname>peagrit</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Oolite is similar in structure, but the concretions are
as small as the roe of a fish.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pisolitic</ent>⟦br⟧
